From: qinf-build <build@qinf.local>
Subject: [PATCH] qinf: sentinel comment proving PATCH_COMMAND wiring

This is a no-op patch that adds a single sentinel comment near the top of
ggml.h. Its purpose is to verify that CMake's FetchContent PATCH_COMMAND is
wired correctly, applies cleanly on first fetch, and is idempotent on
subsequent reconfigures.

Real fused-op patches (PR 4.2.A onward — ggml_deltanet_post_state, etc.)
land alongside this sentinel as separate numbered patch files.

---
 ggml/include/ggml.h | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/ggml/include/ggml.h b/ggml/include/ggml.h
index 0000000..0000000 100644
--- a/ggml/include/ggml.h
+++ b/ggml/include/ggml.h
@@ -1,3 +1,5 @@
+// QINF_PATCH_SENTINEL: this header is patched at FetchContent time by qwen-inference;
+// see patches/ in the qwen-inference repo for the patch series.
 #pragma once

 //
